Sentencas: Undoped BaTiO3 perovskite oxide is more effective than SrTiO3 and La2Ti2O7 oxide as anode catalyst in SOFC fueled with H2S-containing methane.
Titulo: Application of BaTiO3 as anode materials for H2S-containing CH4 fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical performance, impedance spectroscopy and other characterizations show that pure BaTiO3 is a good anode catalyst for conversion of methane in SOFC, especially in H2S-containing atmospheres.
Titulo: Application of BaTiO3 as anode materials for H2S-containing CH4 fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared with SrTiO3 and La2Ti2O7 samples, the BaTiO3-based fuel cell has higher resistance to carbon deposition, better electrochemical performance and much higher stability during long term operation.
Titulo: Application of BaTiO3 as anode materials for H2S-containing CH4 fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A maximum power density of 135 mW cm(-2) was achieved at 900 degrees C with 0.5% H2S-CH4 in a fuel cell having a 300 mu m thick YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Application of BaTiO3 as anode materials for H2S-containing CH4 fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: High catalytic activity for methane conversion, mixed electronic and ionic conductivity, and the surface basicity of BaTiO3 unexpectedly provides promising performance as anodes in SOFC.
Titulo: Application of BaTiO3 as anode materials for H2S-containing CH4 fueled solid oxide fuel cells
